*3@2                          PD Game Review@1 :-@4 ARKANOS*2@1
                          -------------------------
@4
Arkanos,@3 a Break out clone, Similar to Arkanoid's, Pong & the Master of them
all@2 MEGABALL@3. Well a strange selection for me to pick this issue! Normally I
would review an Adventure game, So why the change of Heart?

Well!  Time to admit something, I am addicted to@2 MEGABALL@3 ...I just love the
game  ..And no clone or other BAT & BALL has ever come close to knocking  it
off its perch...Until Now!  Yes!@4 ARKANOS@3 comes a very close second in my Bat
& Ball games TOP TEN.

OK!  The game is programmed in AMOS@1 (Stop cringing)@3 I really don't mind AMOS
games @1 (Providing  they work)@3  and there is not really  much  to  say  about
@4ARKANOS@3  that has not already been said about all the other  games  of  this
type.
@6
                              Brief Description@1
                              -----------------
@5
Old  Hat @1 :-@5 You get a Paddle/Bat...A Ball ..and have to hit the  bricks  to
make them disappear.  As in Megaball and various other games of this nature,
Hit a certain brick and it releases a tile which can either be a@1 "Bonus"@5  or
a @1"Baddie"@5 if you pick it up using the Paddle/Bat.

Nothing  unusual there!  ...Well Arkanos has several features not  in  other
games,  Or in fact it seems to have taken all the good features of  all  the
BAT & BALL games and added them all into 1 game. @1 (A description of all  the
tiles to follow)
@5
One  of  the  interesting points of Arkanos is the@1 "Metal Frame"@5 surrounding
the  Screen.  Its not just your@1 "Run of the Mill"@5 square box,  No!  in  some
levels  it has Projections or Notches@1....@5Which means that if you  Ball  hits
one  it  will  spin  off  in a totally different direction  from  which  you
expect@1..@5This  keeps you on your toes and add interests to the  Overall  game
play.
@6
                                   Graphics@1
                                   --------
@5
THe graphics in Arkanos are of an acceptable standard, Not quite as polished
and Professional as MegaBall, But clear and colourful.
@6
                                    Sound@1
                                    -----@5
Again the sound effects are reasonable,  the Metallic@1 "Clunk" @5 when your ball
hits of the Metal wall sound realistic, as does most of the sound effects.
@6
                                 Playability@1
                                 -----------
@5
Loads  of nice little touches in the game,  to heighten your enjoyment.   You
receive a Password after so many levels@1 (Which means that you don't have  to
play  the Same levels again and again.)@5  Another nice touch is that you  can
play the levels in a Random mode@3" What this means is that levels 1-5 can be
played 4-2-5-1-3 Which strangely enough relieves the boredom if you have  to
constantly play one part over again."
@2
