                           Bonus Tiles Description@1
                           -----------------------
@1
  *)@3 GET KILLED@5  You loose your current paddle. But get 40 points!
                 Always take it if the ball move to the same position
                 instead of loosing the ball with no points. Sorry.
@1
  *)@3 BONUS DOWN@5  Decreases your bonus points by about 200 to 400.
@1
  *@3) BONUS UP @5 Increases your bonus points by about 100 to 300.
@1
  *)@3 HALF BONUS @5 Halfs your bonus points. Oops.
@1
  *)@3 DOUBLE BONUS@5  Doubles your bonus points. Yeah.



@1
  *)@3 RESTART LEVEL@5  Re-initialize current level. If there are only a
                    few special blocks always take it. Otherwise your
                    ball may be trapped, and you must use the DEL key.
@1
  *)@3 SLOW BALL@5  Decreases ball speed by 4. You need more SLOW BALL if
                the speed is about 20 or higher for a better playing
                speed.
@1
  *)@3 CATCH BALL@5  Activates the catch field on your paddle. This is the
                 flashing line at the top of your paddle. If you take
                 this  bonus twice, the catch field will be removed.
@1
  *)@3 EXPAND PADDLE@5  Increases your paddle size by one. This means 16
                    pixel extra space to get the ball. Maximum size
                    is 6, so your paddle is at the most 96 pixel large.
                    (about a third of the total level width)
@1
  *)@3 SHRINK PADDLE@5  Decreases your paddle size by one. You loose 16
                    pixel to catch the ball. Minimum size is 1. It's
                    very hard to get the ball with that short paddle.


@1
  *)@3 BRICKTHROUGH@5  If you take this bonus the ball will move through
                   all blocks, except the SHORT CUT and WALLS. But I
                   must warn you: If there are many BALL SPEED UP blocks,
                   the ball will speed up very fast, and . .  .   .    .
                   Away !!! Take this bonus again, and the ball behaves
                   normal.
@1
  *)@3 ZAP EXPANDER@5  Removes all expanding blocks on the level. Another
                   warning comes up: You can use expanding blocks to
                   break through INDESTRUCT blocks, and if you remove
                   them... 8-)
@1 
  *)@3 ZAP SPECIAL@5  Removes all special blocks. These are BALL SPEED UP,
                  BALL SPEED DOWN, RANDOM DIRECTION and MOVING BLOCK.
                  I think you can always take this bonus. No warning.
@1 
  *)@3 ZAP INDESTRUCT@5  Removes all indestructible attributes of the level.
                     This means: INDESTRUCT will be removed completely,
                     1-HIT INDESTRUCT will be replaced by a normal block
                     (the red one) and all 5-, 4-, 3-, 2-HIT BLOCKS will
                     also be replaced by a normal block (the grey one).



@1
  *)@3 MORE DYNAMITE@5  Expands all exploding blocks, one the each side: up,
                    down, left and right. But remember: exploding blocks
                    only count 8 points. Nevertheless a very effective
                    way to complete a level.
@1
  *)@3 LASER PADDLE@5  Activates the lasers on your paddles. The paddle will
                   change totally. Use left mouse button to fire laser.
                   Don't fire them too often. Every mouse click resets
                   your laser, even if you didn't hit anything. Remember
                   this if you want to fire at blocks on the top of the
                   level.
@1
  *)@3 NEXT LEVEL@5  Brings you to the next level straight away and counts
                 down the left bonus points. Remember all the left points
                 on this level before you take it. Also remember if the
                 next level gets harder. Think quick, if it's worth. ;-)
@1
  *)@3 EXTRA PADDLE@5  Gives you an extra paddle. But removes all extras,
                   like CATCH BALL, LASER PADDLE and BRICKTHROUGH. You
                   also loose 100 bonus points. That's not really bad.


@1
  *)@3 BONUS DIAMONDS@5  There are also 8 different coloured bonus diamonds.
                     If you catch all 8 diamonds you get 3 extra paddles
                     but remember that you take them in toggle mode. One
                     diamond also counts 100 points. It's hard to let
                     them fall down, but you will really need them on
                     higher levels!  8-)


@4
  From level 101 to 200 the bonus tiles will be hidden until they leave
  the level area. So you've just a second to look at it and decide to
  take or not. 
@6
                                   Summary@1
                                   -------
@3
IF  you  are  a  fan of this type of game,  or if you are just  looking  for
something  to entertain you for a couple of hours, #8 GET IT@3.   Arkanos  is  a
Brilliant effort that will not disappoint.The only Negative comment I  would
have regarding Arkanos is.  The#8 16@3 letter password for the levels,  The game
is  free  and I do feel that typing 16 letters in each time a bit excessive,
Other than that an excellent game.



